<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 7:51PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Davie, Iredell and
northwestern Rowan Counties through 845 PM EDT...
At 751 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Statesville, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Mocksville, Troutman, Bermuda Run, Cooleemee, Cleveland,
Harmony, Lake Norman State Park, Stony Point and Fork Church.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
